"title": "5024: inner being",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5024",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The deepest aspects of human nature, known completely by God, to be contrasted with the outward appearance or public image of a person.</p>\n<h2>The contrast of the inner being with the outward person</h2>\n<h3>The desires of the inner being</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:14-Rom7:25\">ROM 7:14–7:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:3-Ps51:6\">PSA 51:3–51:6</a></p>\n<h3>The inner being is not subject to physical constraints</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:7-2Cor4:18\">2CO 4:7–4:18</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The inner being should take priority over the outward person</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:3-1Pet3:4\">1PE 3:3–3:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7\">1SA 16:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:16-Eph3:19\">EPH 3:16–3:19</a></p>",
